The paper proposes a new framework for learning to hash with limited data, which is a common problem in real-world applications. The proposed method is based on transfer learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on image retrieval, which is a common application of hashing in computer vision, suggesting that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of auxiliary data to improve the performance of the hashing method, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes an optimization approach to solve the resultant problem, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
